net.dempsy.messages

Interface MessageProcessorLifecycle<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - is the type of the message processor being managed.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MessageProcessor, MessageProcessor

    public interface MessageProcessorLifecycle<T>

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void activate(T instance, Object key)
      The 'activation' lifecycle phase is invoked by Dempsy after a new instance is instantiated (see newInstance()) and before the message handling is invoked to give the message processor a chance to prepare.
      List<KeyedMessageWithType> invoke(T instance, KeyedMessage message)
      This method is invoked by the framework when a message is ready to be processed by its target message processor 'instance'.
      boolean invokeEvictable(T instance)
      Invokes the evictable method on the provided instance.
      List<KeyedMessageWithType> invokeOutput(T instance)
      This method is invoked by the framework when output is enabled (see isOutputSupported()) and it's time to invoke the output phase of the particular message processor 'instance.'
      boolean isEvictionSupported()
      This method is invoked by Dempsy to determine whether or not the Mps managed by this MessageProcessorLifecycle support being notified of evictions.
      boolean isOutputSupported()
      This method is invoked by Dempsy to determine whether or not the Mps managed by this MessageProcessorLifecycle support an output cycle.
      Set<String> messagesTypesHandled()
      This method is invoked by Dempsy to determine what message types are handled by the processors managed by this MessageProcessorLifecycle.
      T newInstance()
      This lifecycle phase should be implemented to return a new instance of the message processor.
      void passivate(T instance)
      The 'passivation' lifecycle phase is invoked by Dempsy just prior to the framework giving up control of the message processor.
      void start(ClusterId myCluster)
      This method should be implemented to handle carrout out the actual 'start' message processor lifecycle phase.
      void validate()
      The implementor can put validation checks here.

    • Method Detail

      • newInstance

        T newInstance()
       throws DempsyException
        This lifecycle phase should be implemented to return a new instance of the message processor. It will be invoked by Dempsy when it needs a fresh instance. This happens, for eample, when a message is dispatched to a cluster with a key that the framework hasn't seen before.
        Throws:
        DempsyException

      • activate

        void activate(T instance,
              Object key)
       throws DempsyException
        The 'activation' lifecycle phase is invoked by Dempsy after a new instance is instantiated (see newInstance()) and before the message handling is invoked to give the message processor a chance to prepare.
        Throws:
        DempsyException

      • passivate

        void passivate(T instance)
        throws DempsyException
        The 'passivation' lifecycle phase is invoked by Dempsy just prior to the framework giving up control of the message processor. This is done when a message processor is being evicted or in the case of elasticity where it's not managed in the current Node anymore.
        Throws:
        DempsyException

      • invoke

        List<KeyedMessageWithType> invoke(T instance,
                                  KeyedMessage message)
                           throws DempsyException
        This method is invoked by the framework when a message is ready to be processed by its target message processor 'instance'.
        Throws:
        DempsyException

      • invokeOutput

        List<KeyedMessageWithType> invokeOutput(T instance)
                                 throws DempsyException
        This method is invoked by the framework when output is enabled (see isOutputSupported()) and it's time to invoke the output phase of the particular message processor 'instance.'
        Throws:
        DempsyException

      • isOutputSupported

        boolean isOutputSupported()
        This method is invoked by Dempsy to determine whether or not the Mps managed by this MessageProcessorLifecycle support an output cycle.

      • invokeEvictable

        boolean invokeEvictable(T instance)
                 throws DempsyException
        Invokes the evictable method on the provided instance. If the evictable is not implemented, returns false.
        Throws:
        DempsyException

      • isEvictionSupported

        boolean isEvictionSupported()
        This method is invoked by Dempsy to determine whether or not the Mps managed by this MessageProcessorLifecycle support being notified of evictions.

      • messagesTypesHandled

        Set<String> messagesTypesHandled()
        This method is invoked by Dempsy to determine what message types are handled by the processors managed by this MessageProcessorLifecycle.
        Returns:
        the list of message types handled.

      • validate

        void validate()
       throws IllegalStateException
        The implementor can put validation checks here. This method will be invoked by Dempsy when the cluster is started to check for a valid state. This method should NOT be overloaded to intercept the startup. please see start(ClusterId)
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - when the MessageProcessorLifecycle is configured incorrectly

      • start

        void start(ClusterId myCluster)
        This method should be implemented to handle carrout out the actual 'start' message processor lifecycle phase. Please see the User Guild for more information on the message processor lifecycle.
